The 401 Class Mass Hauler is a heavy logistical vessel designed for the transport of large physical cargoes and containerized freight across interplanetary and interstellar routes. It is a derivative of the Imperial Fuel Hauler – 404 Class, repurposed and modified to carry dense materials, machinery, and raw resources instead of promethium and liquid fuels.

The 401’s massive internal holds and reinforced skeletal frame allow it to carry thousands of tons of bulk freight in standardized cargo containers, making it one of the most efficient load-bearing ships in Imperial service. Unlike its 404-class cousin, which relies on insulated tank systems, the 401 employs open-bay cargo modules supported by magnetic clamps and pressure-sealed loading corridors, enabling rapid reconfiguration depending on mission or contract.

Although primarily civilian in design, many Imperial Navy and Munitorum fleets employ 401 Class Haulers as strategic supply vessels, escorted by destroyers and frigates during wartime operations. In frontier sectors and forge world convoys, these ships are essential lifelines, carrying everything from agri-world grain to Mechanicus machinery between stars.

Like all Imperial industry, their design is rugged, reliable, and ancient, a monument to function over form. They are the arteries of the Imperium, slow but vital, keeping the endless machinery of humanity alive among the stars.

Miniature Specs:
Length: 10.1 cm
Mounting: 3 mm

📡 Follow @j.p.m.designs for more industrial voidcraft, haulers, and logistic vessels to expand your Imperial convoys.

R&D had finally had enough of management's shenanigans and decided to take matters into their own hands. The team decided that it was a good idea to try microdosing the shrink ray, but they just ended up shrinking two of the janitors.

When confronted by management, R&D said that they had taken downsizing literally. Once management realized that they could now pay the tiny janitors similarly tiny salaries, they were overjoyed.

The two janitors were not happy, so they decided to stage a hostile takeover of the company. It might take a while though, given that they're only 8mm tall. Their pay was cut, so they're doing this free for the love of the game.

These were made with the original intention of being Light Infantry for the "The Orphaned" faction in Mystic Space, but they could also work as Cyberpunk gangers, cultists, rebel fighters, etc.

This set contains 10 models in 15/18mm/1:100 scale*. All models are Pre-supported**!

There are 6 troopers equipped with rifles, and 4 different special weapons (meant to be a Compact Smolder Rifle, Spark Rifle, Trace Gun, and Injector Support Weapon).

Mystic Space is a game by Nordic Weasel Games/Ivan Sorensen. These figures are released under version 1.00 of the Mystic Space Commercial License. You can get the alpha version of the rules here:
https://www.wargamevault.com/product/521390/Mystic-Space-Alpha-version?src=hottest

*These models are very much "Heroic Scale". They are roughly 16-17mm to the eyes, and 18-19mm to the top of the head. This was done to reflect the size of the average Star Born in the Mystic Space lore.

**I test print all my pre-supported files. I tend to go with more supports to be safe. I'd recommend using the hot-water technique to ensure easy support removal.

Imbued with excess and pain, the imagination of the dark mechanics forged the Sirenbow class Stalker.
Walking guns, they stalk across the battlefield picking off targets before they know it.

This kit includes everything you need to build a Sirenbow Stalkers in 8mm or AT scale.
The main body measures about the height of the standard Stalker.
This can be built in any number of ways, the kit is flexible with the legs and body being posable.

The kit includes, amongst standard components:
- 2 different feet
- 3 tail weapon options

Four files include:
1. Supported: individual components to print and pose as you desire.
2. Unsupported: as above but supported.
3. Complete: some example builds which you can use as an example or print as a single object. Supported versions included.

The model has been made to go on a 50mm bases and this has been included.


All files come supported and unsupported.

Pictures of models are test prints.
Pictured in the background are the [Rapture Heavy Stalkers](https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/rapture-heavy-stalkers-8mm)

This is an Imperial Stormtrooper scaled for the Epic-scale wargame Star Wars: Regiment.
It is scaled at about 1:285 or 6mm scale and also 1:182 or 10mm.
This trooper is intended for a 25mm round base with infantry stand holes (you can find some to print here: https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:7079406)

I printed this on my Saturn 4 Ultra, at this scale it is highly recommended to print in resin. I have included pre-supported files for both sizes.
This model was created using an image produced by ChatGPT, inputted into Hitem3D, and then manually sculpted, rigged and posed in Blender.
Over time I will add additional poses to this file to give the unit more variety in basing. I thought the result was interesting enough to share as a work-in-progress.

**Star Wars: Regiment** is an epic-scale modification of *Star Wars: Legion*, modified for fielding full infantry companies, and vehicle platoons in large cinematic battles. The game supports 6mm (1:285) scale miniatures, with free STLs for 3D printing, full digital support through Tabletop Simulator and a web-based army builder.

Genetically engineered Marines travel throughout Space, battling depraved heretics, dishonourable traitors, and vile aliens.

This set includes 4 powered gauntlets, two holding the torn off heads of two different types of alien beast - a brutal ork, and a sinister soulstealer. The third holds a retro style space beaky helmet, and the fourth is empty, perhaps for you to add in your own head model! All four have supported versions.

This is an updated version of the first thing I ever tried to 'sculpt', as opposed to arrange geometric shapes - an ork head. It's a little reflection on my part, comparing where I started to where I am. It's been a slow process, as I take what digital hobby time I can in between physical modelling and all my other fickle interests! But it's still nice to see what I feel in some improvement.

You can see the original here:
https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/power-gauntlet-prime-scale-powered-gauntlet-holding-head

I am an amateur enthusiast 3D designer, and appreciate all constructive feedback. Please check out my other designs for more wargame models, and please consider following me, posting a make, or even leaving a donation via my profile!

 The Tortuga Group, a heretofore relatively unknown defense contractor, recently unveiled an upgrade suite for the venerable Quixote-class mech chassis.

 Their Quixote Defense Upgrade Package is a long-distance take on the concept of mechanized walker warfare, with an emphasis on stand-off weaponry and heavy shielding. This may not be suited for the mechanized arenas of Junctionworld, but mercenaries on the open battlefields found throughout the worldgate networks are sure to benefit.

 The new Spina Mk.II C-Beam Cannon is devastatingly effective on distance targets, with the damage inflicted usually an inverse to the target’s proximity.

 For closer adversaries that slip past the C-Beamer, a Redmaw Persecutor-class Plasma Cannon dispenses superheated damage, though its recharge rate has caught some pilots short. Thus, a heavy flamethrower is also added to the Spina Mk.II for supplemental in-close coverage.

 Adding to the new upgrade’s enhancements is the Testudo VI Force Field projector, a variation on shielding systems found on heavier kaiju-fighting megamechs and titans. When properly modulated, this generator can be used to deflect heavy incoming fire, or lend its protection to nearby units.

---------------------------------------------

This kit includes...

1 Plasma Cannon with two optional barrels.
1 C-Beamer Cannon with Auxiliary Flamethrower
2nd Generation Weapon Arms and Upper Arms with support rims to add stability.
1 Force Field Generator with two options of flat magnetized mount or a peg compatible with Imperial Warrior and similar builds.

Enjoy!

Best,
John Bear Ross

‘Isurus pattern’ Dire Wolf Titan armour, Loyalist allegiance, made to fit the LI/Adeptus Titanicus Dire Wolf Titan.

This is a full set of armour plates, to give your Dire Wolf titans a whole new look.

Are you a follower of the Warmaster? Then you’ll want the traitor version here:
https://cults3d.com/:2909778

Looking for a version with a plain, unaligned trim? Then go here:
https://cults3d.com/:2909807

This is a complete kit, replacing all of the armour plates.
Please note that, to utilise the carapace plate(s), you will need to cut GW part 21, just behind the vent, to remove the original carapace plate from the rest of this part before assembling the titan skeleton. Rest assured, it's a very simple cut - see the final photos for reference.

Included are 2 versions of the carapace, split and unsplit. The file '...unsplit' is the carapace in a single piece. The 3-part version is made up of 2 files, '...side' (which you copy and mirror) and '...top'.
The finished carapaces are exactly the same. Printing is faster with the split version (not so tall on the build plate) and tends to give a better surface finish (orientation to build plate). The unsplit version takes longer but, as it's a single piece, is much more robust and easier to swap in and out on your titan.

Most parts feature magnet holes, for either 2mm dia or 5x2x0.5mm magnets, giving the option of painting multiple versions for parts that you can swap in and out. Many can grip to the titan frame without the need for magnets (thigh plate and unsplit carapace feature holes, but you may well find you don't really need them. Shoulder plates on the other hand would need magnetising to be swappable). You'll need to add the appropriate reciprocal magnet holes/magnets to your titan skeleton to make use of these.

Files included: STL, pre-supported STL and Lychee scenes of each part (in the ZIP file) - should you want/need to tweak the supports for your particular printer.

Notes:
This is for the 8mm, AT2018/LI version only and is scaled appropriately for this size.
STLs and supported STLs are for left side versions only of the engine cover, shoulder, shin and thigh plates. These should be copied and mirrored to produce the right side plates (Shin plate is symmetrical, so can just copied), when printing your full set - though the '...full set' Lychee scene included in the ZIP file has this already set up for you. This full set scene utilises the 3-part version of the carapace, so swap these out for the 'unsplit' carapace if you want to print the single piece version with the rest of the parts.

This looks _suspiciously_ like my [Modular Utility Building](https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:6838588), don't you think? 
OK, yeah, I fancied having one that was full height - that is, the same height as a GW Sector Fronteris hab block, and therefore also the same height as a [Fronteris style bunker](https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:6988922). It is, very approximately, 60x60x70mm.
For my own use I thought I'd go all in on the vents; make it some sort of cooling tower type thing, with a simple style vaguely influenced by some belfry louvres. I've kept in some more basic walls too, if that's more your style (or you plan to embellish them yourself).

### Compatibility

Style-wise, it obviously takes heavy cues from the Sector Fronteris hab units.

The pipe ports are the standard size expected on GW's 40k terrain - 25.6mm diameter.

The side pipe ports have a centre-line height of 14.5mm, which matches other terrain, e.g. Thermic Plasma Conduits.. Their outer face is 30.5mm from the centre point, so if you have two opposite each other they'll be 61mm apart, which should be a familiar size to those used to e.g. Sector Mechanicus components.

The roof is the same height as that of a Sector Fronteris hab unit, and the roof with a port should match the ports on those hab units too.

### Assembly

You will need:
* 4x *pillars*
* 4x *walls*
* 1x *roof*
If you chose walls with *ports*, you'll also need
* 1+ *pipe ends*

Walls push into pillars from behind. I recommend putting the roof in unglued as you put together the rest, then gluing it in last.

Pillars can be mirrored for a bit more variety.

### Pre-supports

The supported files here are the way I did them for myself, successfully. Is it the best? No. The walls and pillars are definitely over-supported, but I wasn't going to go back and change something that worked.

As you may see from the pictures, I did _not_ print non-louvred walls. The supports have been applied in the same way, but I have not actually printed these specifically.

### FAQ

* What's with the extra holes on the pipe ports in the photos but not on the STLs?
 _I have bizarre hopes of putting a lot of magnets everywhere. I'm not doing this in a way that I think makes sense to most people, so I didn't think it was worth sharing those. You can have the clean ones that actually look good by themselves!_

Hello everyone,
The Advent season is all about joy and giving, and I think it's just part of it to give others a little joy.

First of all, I would like to sincerely thank everyone who has supported me on Patreon over the past few years. Without your support, I probably wouldn't have taken the time to create some of my miniatures. It was a great motivation that helped me move forward - thank you so much!
But the time on Patreon has passed due to a lack of time. The fact that you have the opportunity to download these old publications today is primarily thanks to them.

<b>MyLinks: https://allmylinks.com/enfenix</b>

---
<p>General information</p>

My miniatures are designed to work out of the box with original 28mm Hero Quest miniatures.
I always add a version with Heroquest base and one without a base. The weapons and the base are only combined (if possible). If you need different HeroQuest-style base, you should check out my customizer:
https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:4299465

Personally, I now prefer 32mm miniatures. I usually scale them to 112% -115% directly in the slicer.

I am happy about every shared make, especially the painted ones.
By the way i love espresso, so don't hesitate to leave a tip if you like =D

If you are inexperienced with slicer setting, I recommend this one for ...
Ender 3: https://www.fatdragongames.com/fdgfiles/cura-ender-3-5-profiles-work-cr-10/
Bambu A1 Printer: https://www.fatdragongames.com/fdgfiles/bambu-studio-slicer-profiles-a1-mini-3d-printer/

‘Isurus pattern’ Warhound Titan armour, Traitor allegiance, made to fit the Adeptus Titanicus Warhound Titan.

This is a full set of armour plates, to give your Warhounds a whole new look.
Are you are Loyalist player? Then check out the loyalist-themed version here:
https://cults3d.com/:2382548

Looking for a version with a plain, unaligned trim? Then go here:
https://cults3d.com/:2382534

Carapace and Groin plate STLs have recesses for 5x2x0.5mm magnets, with 2mm dia magnet holes in the Shoulder plate, for easy magnetising. Shin plate features clip to hold in securely. Thigh plate fits into existing gap on the titan skeleton.

Files included: STL, pre-supported STL and Lychee scenes (in the ZIP file) - should you want/need to tweak the supports for your particular printer.

Notes:
This is for the 8mm, AT2018 version.
STLs and supported STLs are for left side versions only of the shoulder and thigh plates. Shin plate is symmetrical, and so can be mirrored or just copied. These should be copied and/or mirrored to produce the right side plates, when printing your full set.
Also included in the ZIP is a Lychee file that has all the plates, as well as the appropriate duplicated/mirrored parts, within the scene too - this is the file appended ‘...Full Scene’)

There has always been the question:

Why does the Empire have steam tanks, supposedly based on dwarven technology, and the dwarves don't? Well not anymore! The dwarf arms race continues! (and it's not going to stop, I warn you) and today I bring you this powerful steam tank 100% dwarf design!

This pack contains void trooper leaders equipped with various pistols and melee weapons. There are 3 different pistol options (laser pistol, plasma pistol, and rivet pistol), and 3 different melee options (sword, power fist, harpoon). Each combination of pistol and melee weapon is represented in a distinct pose, so there are 9 total models!

If you want to see a certain weapon combination, but in a different pose (for example; you like the pose of the plasma+harpoon, but want the plasma pistol swapped out with a laser pistol) just let me know and I'll put it together and upload it!

<>

There are both unsupported, and pre-supported* versions of each, including Lychee files.

*I tend to go heavier on the supports (I'd rather spend a little more time cleaning up supports than have a failure and have to completely re-print it). I use the "hot water method" for removing supports to make it easier. I can't guarantee it will work for all printers and resin though.

Justification du tag SUP :

There are both unsupported, and pre-supported* versions of each, including Lychee files.

15mm scale elite sci-fi troopers in fully sealed armored suits carrying special weapons.

This pack contains 9 total models, 3 poses each of Flamethrowers, Grenade Launchers, and Plasma Guns (but they could also be used as melters, or other sci-fi energy weapons).

There are both unsupported, and pre-supported* versions of each, including Lychee files.

*I'm not a professional at this, but I've test printed them and they all came out good for me. I tend to go heavier on the amount of supports, but if you use the "hot water method" they should come off easily.

The design is loosely inspired by "auxiliary" troops that would fight in the era of galactic conquest and civil war 30,000 years in the future...
However, I wanted to make them look more strange and ancient, like they are from a semi-mythologized event that took place 10,000 years in the past. These should also work well in other sci-fi, or even steampunk, weird-war, or post apocalyptic settings.

You can download FREE samples of many of these models here: https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/archaic-void-troopers-basic-troops-sample-15mm

Elite sci-fi troopers in fully sealed armored suits. The design is loosely inspired by "auxiliary" troops that would fight in the era of galactic conquest and civil war 30,000 years in the future...
However, I wanted to make them look more strange and ancient, like they are from a semi-mythologized event that took place 10,000 years in the past. These should also work well in other sci-fi, or even steampunk, weird-war, or post apocalyptic settings.

This pack contains 30 total models. 10 each with basic laser guns, lasers guns with a power cable and backpack, and SMG-ish guns.

There are both unsupported, and pre-supported* versions of each, including Lychee files.
<<The SMG variants are not yet fully pre-supported. I ran out of resin before I could finish test printing them. They WILL be updated soon!>>

These are my first full models modeled completely on my own, so if you find any problems please let me know!

*I tend to go heavier on the supports (I'd rather spend a little more time cleaning up supports than have a failure and have to completely re-print it). I use the "hot water method" for removing supports, and didn't have any problems or noticeable scarring. I can't guarantee it will work for all printers and resin though.

Justification du tag SUP :

There are both unsupported, and pre-supported* versions of each, including Lychee files. «The SMG variants are not yet fully pre-supported. I ran out of resin before I could finish test printing them. They WILL be updated soon!»

The full set containing unsupported and Pre-Supported versions of all 10 poses of all 3 weapon variants are available here for a small price: https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/archaic-void-troopers-basic-troops-full-set-15mm

These are my first full models modeled completely on my own, so if you find any problems please let me know!

*I tend to go heavier on the supports (I'd rather spend a little more time cleaning up supports than have a failure and have to completely re-print it). I use the "hot water method" for removing supports, and didn't have any problems or noticeable scarring. I can't guarantee it will work for all printers and resin though.

A humble reworking of Moonjammy's excellent designs, optimised for stackable printing.

Love printing little dudes but hate having to get up every hour to scrape off your build plate, waste good resin in your wash station, and restart the print? Then here's the new easy-to-use stacking solution you've been waiting for! Stack small objects vertically to fit into your print schedule, or efficiently fill left over build plate volume when printing taller objects.

Including:
- **Galactic Crusader Infantry in Heavy Siege Armour** with a choice of Boxing Gloves or Hedge Trimmers and a selection of heavy weaponry
- Arranged in pre-built stacks of 12, 18 and 24.
- Raw components and a guide for creating custom stacks

**Scale and Sizing:**
The Galactic Crusaders in this pack have been resized to 105%.
This makes the average Galactic Crusader ~9.5mm tall (varying based on pose and armour style), and the base plugs 6.16x1.31mm.

**Want to know more about Floating Rafts and you can use them to convert your own models into stackable designs?**

A humble reworking of the very concept of a raft, optimised for vertical printing.

Floating Rafts are small self-supporting structures that establish platforms parallel with but above the build plate.
This allows you to take models that have been supported for standard printing (or even auto-supported) and quickly convert them into stackable designs with minimal effort!
While individually small, Floating Rafts can be combined side by side to form wider rafts, or even mirrored front-to-back to create much larger rafts suitable for small scale vehicles, or larger scale components like helmets, shoulder pads and weapons for 28mm models.

**Wait, what's the point in stacking prints? Isn't that just a waste of resin?**

Stacking prints incurs a small amount of additional resin use, but brings a number of big advantages:
- You can scale a large number of small print jobs up into bigger print jobs. i.e. You can run one overnight 8h print instead of six or seven 1h30m prints, each of which need to be scraped off the build plate, cleaned, etc, before they can be re-run.
- You can scale small objects to fit in with the largest objects on your build plate. i.e. If you are printing a 28mm vehicle with parts that are 80mm tall, arrange smaller parts in 80mm stacks to make best use of a long print. This allows you to use small amounts of leftover build plate space to print large numbers of components!
- You can _slightly_ decrease overall print times, as stacked components can be kept very close to their floating rafts.


**How do I use this?**

Take any traditionally supported (or even auto-supported!) object that fits within an area you are able to create with Floating Rafts.

1.a. Replace the existing raft with platform made from Floating rafts.
1.b. Optionally shorten the existing supports to 1-2mm. Traditionally objects are raised 5mm above the build plate to avoid raft collision, but that's not necessary when you're up in the stacks!
_(I typically use Blender for this, but you could use subtraction in Windows 3D Builder or a simple Planar Cut in your slicer!)_
2. Stack your objects on central supports.
_(I embed the floating rafts in central support pillars, but for peak resin efficiency, why not try embedding the rafts in something you are planning to print anyway, like the undersides of bases!)_
3. Print!


**Okay, that's great, but where the models at?**

Don't worry, I'll be sharing a number of packs with small-scale (and maybe not so small scale) models I worked on while experimenting with this process, which should give you some useful models to print and ideas for how to use this concept.

*Like what I'm doing? [Buy me a cup of resin!](https://ko-fi.com/lstar)* 😁

Mixing the darkest of magics with the fires of the Bull God, the Fire Elemental Demons are born for destruction and little else!

When fully assembled these Fire Elemental Demons stand about 60mm tall. They are designed to go on 40mm bases.
This is a multipart kit for an incredible amount of variety to your units. It contains:
- 4 torsos
- 6 heads plus a unit champion (has a big hat/crown and chain beard)
- 2 upper bodies, these can be mirrored
- 3 lower bodies, these can be mirrored
- 6 weapons, these can be mirrored and used for either hand

Files come pre-supported and unsupported.

Happy printing!

ASSEMBLY
- Good to print a variety of parts, most things should dry fit to a point so you can get the poses just right.
- I recommend glueing together one Fire Demon at a time. This way you can plan the next Fire Demon so they rank up nicely (I did my best however to give the right balance between pose and variety).

Pictures of models are test prints.

A humble reworking of Speacock and THEWRAETHTHU's excellent reworking of Failtruck's (?) excellent design, optimised and cleaned up for easy printing.

"_While P.O.D. Droplets were usually synonymous with lightning assaults, one of their most infamous uses during the Hera-C involved an over-eager commander ordering the launch of a wave long before his logistics ships had made it into orbit._

_When the P.O.D.s finally made planetfall some six months later, the confused defenders found nothing inside but dust and emaciated corpses..._"

- Reassembled and repaired: No more voids!
- Hollowed for efficient printing: Including rafts and supports, small P.O.D.s use ~3.8ml of resin, large P.O.D.s use ~5.4ml of resin
- Includes supported and unsupported STLs and Lychee scenes for tweaking

OK, just a scooped, supported and magnet ready version of Wolfkeeper's GRIMDARK MINUTE FLYING ARMED TRANSPORT and nitramthx's burning little dino for galactic crusaders. They are great little free files and will work well at 8mm. I sized them to have roughly a 70mm wingspan, but size however you like, just be cognicent that resizing circles can make ovals.

I removed the lower floor of the model, so the magent insert is on the roof of the model and can accept magnets up to 10mm - so pick your poison.

I also did some editing to make sure there were no resin captures.

These models are not hollowed in the traditional sense - no resin can be captured and all internals can be exposed to UV light for curing. Some idiot will not look at the files and mis-understand that and will invariably do an "aktuallly blah blah blah" - it always seems to happen....

All your sponson needs, all in one place!

A central collection so I don't have to update a half dozen packs when modifying the sponsons, and the Universal Sponson Pin needed for the Magnetic Sponson System.

**Wait a minute, Magnetic Sponson System?**

The Magnetic Sponson System is an easy way to swap out sponson weapons. Want to change up loadouts between battles, or need to replace a snapped barrel? Just slide the old sponsons out and new ones in!

Each pin has slots for a normal sponson weapon and a 2x1mm neodymium magnet.

The pins are symmetrical, so there is no need to mirror them. Just remember the rivets point backwards, and make sure to decide on which polarity to use for the left and right pins!

**Note:** This is currently compatible with the Pred-8R, SIG-RN, and Crete-S packs.

*Like what I'm doing? [Buy me a cup of resin!](https://ko-fi.com/lstar)* 😁

A slightly unhinged reworking of Moonjammy's excellent design, optimised for _crazy_ printing!

A new concept for creating simple, stackable supports for Epic scale infantry! Use the supplied STLs or easily create blocks of infantry in any arbitrary width and height simply by copying strips in Lychee and moving them vertically, no additional fine-tuning required!

**ARE STACKABLE SUPPORTS RIGHT FOR ME?**

Stackable supports are slightly less resin-efficient compared with printing a single squad flat on the build plate, but time and clean-up efficient, allowing you to print large numbers of troops in a single print without having to get up to scrape them off the build plate, clean up, and restart your print every hour!

Stackable supports also allow you to make effective use of empty space on your build plate when printing larger vehicles or 28mm scale models. Just create a stack as tall as your other models!

**UH OH, THIS LOOKS COMPLICATED! IS REMOVING THE SUPPORTS HARD?**

De-supporting these is easy and risk free!
The heavy supports only make contact with the pseudo-rafts so you can yank them off without any worries. Then just use a knife tip or tweezer to pick off the remaining supports on the individual models.

*Love playing games with hidden orders but hate faffing around with flimsy carboard tokens?
Streamline your games of Legions Imperialis (or Epic!) with these X-Wing-style order dials!
Just add two 3x2mm neodymium magnets and get scheming!*

Note: This is a bit of an open beta for dial designs I've been working on recently.
If other people like these as much as I do, I'll release a full range, covering other games, and fancy designs to suit various factions and armies.
Let me know how you get on printing these, if you run into any problems, or have any suggestions for making them better!


**How should I print these?**

These dials are supported for easy and high-quality vertical printing on a resin printer.
Unsupported versions are included in case this doesn't suit you.

Aligned vertically, layer height is more important for fine detail than your printer's XY resolution, so these designs should print nicely even on older printers! I recommend using a 0.03mm layer height.

**How should I remove these weird supports?**

Like other supports, warm them up with some warm water or a heat gun before removal. Wiggle the supports back and forth and they should pop off.

In most cases this should leave next to no support marks, but if a small amount of material is left on the disc, rub them gently with some sandpaper, or scrape them with a knife/mouldline remover.

**Why are there 5 versions of the lower discs? Aren't they exactly the same?**

This is to prevent any mentats or Alpha Legion infiltrators you happen to play against from trying to predict your orders by analysing icon or support mark orientation!

**Any painting tips?**

Option 1: Paint the dials and use a pinwash to pick out the symbols and text. Oil washes work great for this!

Option 2: Paint the dials and drybrush/overbrush the raised surfaces with another colour, leaving your original colour in the recesses.

**Any tips for reducing wear and tear?**

These things are going to get handled, tossed about and rubbed together over the course of a game!

I recommend giving your paint plenty of time to fully dry unjoined before use, and to apply a good coat of varnish!

**Are you going to make a version for my favourite army/game system?**

Yep, I've already designed dials for other games like Epic, Battlefleet Gothic and Aeronautica Imperialis, and themes for a number of popular armies. If the feedback for this pack is good, I'll release others in due course!

**I don't want to wait. Can I make my own versions?**

Sure, feel free to remix the Blank version for personal use.

The Elven Caestopaeifs served their world well, giving many weapons painstakingly designed. However, most of the schools of such crafters hide dark secrets.Being obedient to wise gravekeeping seers, they prepare carcasses for rituals comparable with grave-robbery. The spirits of the fallen warriors occupy cold animated statues of tough eldritch material to fight against alien occupants, so the living Elves could hear songs of joy ever again. Monsoon Warhost of Beal-Tanny remember the desperate action to revive dead exile brethren from their defiled Kurghans on paradise world of Taran, so they could avenge on aliens as mighty undead gargantuans in the war.

The Smallwraith models are made using model builder by Karadryel (https://cults3d.com/en/users/Karadryel/3d-models)
The Ligma Razor model is a free model by Spear Miniatures
(https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/d-reaper-gun-only)

UPDATE:
2023 August 15th - separate legs for CQC Smallwraith models added, now the models have new Phantom Swords and Spook Bardiche objects appropriate for printing in 8mm scale.

NOTICE:
- the models are not tested yet, there’re no supported stls required for safe printing, so the prints are required for experienced hobbyists;
- model sturdiness, especially Phantom Swords variants, is questionable;
- the preview images are dated.

THANKS TO:
Mannschaft for Smallwraith models test printing and reporting for flaws found;
MKhand_Industries for supporting and suggesting ideas (https://cults3d.com/en/users/Mkhand_Industries/creations)

Gore Krushas are build by the biggest and craziest meks at the peak of a greenskin WAAAAAGH! as a symbol of their gods - Towering over the battlefield this 'eavy armored walker krushes smaller enemies by simply stomping them to bloody goo (with insane laughter from the Gore Kursha Kaptin').
Meanwhile larger targets can be engaged with it's mega chain choppa, ripping through armor easily.
Although not very accurate, the Gore Krushas ranged weapons have 'nuff shootin' to hit and kill all targets. The sound of high kaliber gattlas at full auto bursts is horrifying or at least intimidating for the most enemies (....or motivating in case of greenskin ears)


FOR BEST QUALITY PRINT, PLEASE READ ALL(!) OF BELOW:

To print the Gore Krusha Mega Walker, you need time or a large resin printer ;-)
I REALLY recommend a layer high of 0.075 or lower for all parts to get the quality I intended.
Please see the pics, those are all printed in FDM (<=0,075mm)!

I tried to keep the need of tree supports low, but I recommend it to use them on some parts - decide for yourself & make sure to set the tree support z-distance to a multiple of 2 (layer hight) for optimal removal (keep in mind: layer hight 0.05 to 0.075(!) )
(The Mega Choppa should be printed with tree support, I included a version with the teef supported, this is also tested)

----------------------------------------------------------------------
-------------- EXCEPTIONAL 'fings for this model: --------------------
----------------------------------------------------------------------

---------- SPIKES ----------

Print them "laying", not standing, or else they will easily snap of if you ram another model ;-)

---------- Exhausts ----------

"GoreKrusha_Exhausts02_Bars_1.75mmFilament.stl" can be combined with "GoreKrusha_Exhausts02.stl" for Resin printers.
In FDM just use some 1.75mm filament & make sure you don't snap of the middle post - trust me :D

---------- LEGS ----------

The legs can be posed standing or walking, but I recommend standing for both to find a good balance for the model.

---------- ARMS ----------

- !!! All joints MUST be printed laying flat !!! This is important, else they will likely snap of due to the weight of the arms.
- The arms should fit thight, but they are not perfect, better glue them after posing
- The ammo belt is a "flexi" print-in-place, once finished, you can gently move the joints to breake it free. With this, the dakka arm can be posed freely as you want.

---------- DA RIGGAZ (Crew) ----------

- Da Riggaz are posed and remixed from https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:3985624 by poikilos
- To print Da Riggaz you need tree supports, I flipped them back 15° or 30° (depending on the model) and lifted them +1,5mm on the Z-axies, so the supports will pe printed first. Layer hight 0.05mm, enable support roof with ~0.75mm.

---------- Over all printing recommendation! ----------

- I printed the bottom plate with 25% infill, since it has to carry the weight of the model (about 1,2kg!)
- Many parts have a "flat surface" -> face those to the build plate.
- Detaild sides / most visible sides should be faced towards the cooling fan.

---------- ASSEMBLY ----------

If you need instructions - just open all files in 3D Builder or e.g. Meshmixer. There you can look where they go.


---------- FOLLOWING: ----------

Shame less beggin' for some coins for coffein I need doin' stuff like that :-)

Please consider a tip ....this highly detailed model was a work of 200h+ of free time over almost a year!
If you do so, I HIGHLY APPRECIATE YOUR GENEROSITY :-)

Kind regards,
Tersus

Not the best weapon for Smaller Knights, but I am a completionist. This is the last one on my list.

The C-Beamer is a relic weapon usually overlooked because it does more damage the farther away the target is, and less up close, which is a disadvantage on the close-range, terrain-choked tabletops of the current edition.

But, it's free. ;)

Supported versions have a lot of tiny sub-supports that you will want to flick out after curing, especially on barrel 3. It seemed the only way to save that spiraling effect.

You might not be able to access or paint the interior cages of barrels 2 or 3. If that is unacceptable, I recommend barrel 1. It's cleaner and sleeker.

Everything is included from the shoulder socket down.

Ball and socket upper arms are included, in case you want to keep a fixed, glued pose.

I recommend the flat-elbowed upper arms, and magnetizing with an 8mm x 2mm or 8mm x 3mm neodymium magnet glued to the fused upper arm, and steel magnets glued to the elbow "socket" of the weapon.

I usually glue a steel BB in the socket, then cap it with a pair of glued-on steel washers. See pics for reference.

You'll lose some poseability, but gain modularity.

Our biggest project is alive!


The challenge was to create a AT scale and a 40K scale hyperdetailed Imperator titan remix.


- The model is a remix from only public or free STLs so it can be shared freely


- The titan is inspired in the Titandeath novel cover, with flat upper platform and gothic style similar to the old classic Epic design.


- Size: 25 cms. for AT, for 40K, following FW scale, it should have a hight of 95-105 cms. so you should upscale the models at 400% or use the 40K scale version. You can upscale it up to 2mts to keep with the lore.


- The base used model is the old epic imperator model, a fantastic and totally accurate model from creator dantigibus you can find (yet) free on cults Here: https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/titan-imperator


- The other base model is the imperator titan, modern-style, from creator zammerak you can find also free here in Cults: https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/titanic-church-delivery-system


- The first part finished was the head, 40K scale with detailed interiors you can download here in Cults in my collection. This release features a AT scale head with no interiors.


- Inside the .zip file you can find a construction guide.





- If you want to know the history of this project, step by step, go to my web page: http://inquisitorweb.mygamesonline.org in the crazy mixer section.





- I'm trying to cut the 40K scale parts to fit Saturn printers. By now, the larger part fits in Saturn 2 printer. Some bigger ones could not fit in the old Saturn.





- Enjoy! and remember donations are always welcome! help us further development of this model.





WARNING! This is a very challenging model, only suitable for very experienced printers and modellers.





Users with a 8K printer may choose to use the 40K version for AT downscaling every part to -400%.





Changelog:





17-4-22: Reinforced the base of the platform down spires, they were too thin for printing in a 2K printer.


18-4-22: Rebuild the upper gun towers. Some people had issues printing them, so I,ve splitted each tower in 2 parts (3 for the back towers) and extra-repair both of them.


Now the problems seems to be solved.


24-4-22: Added 2 optional buildings, a tower bridge in front of the main basillica, and a curved bridge tower for the sides.


27-4-22: last updates, 2 small optional towers for the central place in the platform (place at your choice), replacement fences for the tiny torso fences (sides and back) and church circular fences that don't print well in 2K printers and also replacements for the tiny tower windows.


And as a reward only for my kindly donators, an optional landing pad for the back of the platform with a Arvus lighter included! Ask me for the parts.


27-8-22 Added a set of alternative arms for the main weapons, created by Andrew Killoch


30-10-22 Added a file with the ongoing 40K scale parts, WIP. just now only leg armour, feet and part of the bastion.


6-11-22 Added an alternative 2 parts splitted AT scale torso for smaller printers and uploaded the last leg parts in 40K scale. Now, the legs are complete in 40K scale. and made to the max detail limits my (rather old) computer allows me.


11-11-22 Plasma anihilator complete in 40K scale, find it in the 40K scale file.


20-11-22 Hellstorm cannon complete in 40K scale,find it in the 40K scale file.


3-12-22 Added the head for 40K scale, a revision from my Imperator head model in Cults, size reduced to fit the Imperator body to AT X 4, more detailed and with a simplified top with better fit with the lower middle parts. The head comes without crew.


Also in the main weapons folders you can find both arms (take care, they are different, not mirrors).


4-12-22 Added a 40K scale head variation with crew integrated (2 moderatii and 1 princeps) in the donators rewards folder.


14-12-22 Added a 40K scale Chaos head variant in the donators folder with demonic crew inside.


16-12-22 The 40K torso parts are complete! splitted to fit in a Saturn S or Saturn 2 printer. Added too an alternative part with a secret toaster repair dock in the donators folder. Enjoy!


18-12-22 Added the left feet missing parts (the feet part 4 isn't a mirror from the right one)


5-2-23 Plattform base in 40K scale released! with optional tower splitted parts. As usual parts are splitted to fit larger printers as Saturn 2.


5-3-23 Main cathedral, the first platform building finished!


20-3-23 Started painting the AT scale printed prototype


15-4-23 The Quake cannon Bastion, second platform bulding, finished


21-4-23 Next set of platform buildings ready in 40K scale: Volcano cannon tower and small side church (X2).


2-5-23 Finished the Optional rounded bridge in 40K scale with his rail AA gun and the optional small bridge too.


8-5-23 Last platform buldings finished: front and rear towers and side small tower. Also added in the donators rewards folder a new, remixed Arvus lighter and the optional rear landing platform in 40K scale.


9-5-23 Model finished!!!! yuhuuu!!! last 40K scale parts: the towers under the platform and the hips version 2 (without the emblematic dick cannon)


10-5-23 Added an optional right torso part 6 variant with mechanicum WC and amno rooms in the donators reward forlder.


17-5-23 Added an optional left torso part 4 variant with mechanicum vending machine in the donators reward forlder and repair some minor errors in front and rear towers lower parts (front tower part 1 and rear tower part 3)


19-5-23 Repaired some minor errors in left leg bastion part 3 and added some more details.


22-5-23 Add an alternative AA gun for the platform, more detailed, remixed from redzabo free model on Cults

Join me on Patreon! patreon.com/yasashiikyojinstudio

Giant boars, much like regular boars, travelled in groups known as "sounders." The number of giant boars in a sounder varied, but oftentimes it totalled up to eight. Unlike ordinary pigs, giant boars were vicious and would attack any creature that approached, typically trying to charge their opponents and gore them with their tusks.

Giant Boar for use in any epic adventure! Compatible with D&D and tabletop role-playing games.

Pre-supported version (for resin printing) in 32mm and 54mm scaling options provided!

If you like what I do and would like to support the creation of minis for the whole community please consider joining my Patreon where you can get 50% OFF the entire store, vote for what I sculpt next, get early access to new designs, stat blocks, vtt tokens and a heap more!

This is a hilariously upscaled howitzer-type weapon for your gigantic future war robot.

Note that this is just the gun, to attach it to the original gigantic future war robot you'll need the upper arm piece (which is available for free on my profile).

Despite how it looks, the threading on the barrel and the accelerator coils both are actually designed to print in one piece and be self-supporting when elevated to about 30 degrees or so. Just make sure the rails, piston rods and the actual body of the gun are suitably supported to prevent warping and you should be good to go.

It's available in both Right (A) and Left (B) versions, with the main weapon body having a choice of stick or drum magazine.

Also, one of my heavy stubby gatlings is incorporated into the design. That asymmetric part of the design is a nice feature, in my opinion.

A pair of weapon arms, long and short, are supplied, as well as upper arms at a variety of angles for magnetization.

I glue the ball and sockets together, then glue 12mm x 2mm magnets to the bottom of the upper arm.

An 8mm x 2mm magnet will fit in the face of the main weapon body. I usually glue in washers in the barrel section. 4mm inner diameter/9mm outer diameter washers usually do it, or #6 washers. Or just glue them together and print more.

You can use opposing magnets in the weapon arms (remember opposite poles) to the new upper arms. I recommend 12mm x 3mm magnets.

Enjoy, and thanks again! More good stuff to come.

Best,
JBR

P.S. Check out my other Knight parts, most of which are free.
https://cults3d.com/en/users/johnbearross/creations

P.P.S. I started a Discord server for feedback and for folks to follow progress of my sculpts.
https://discord.gg/NJtm78rF63

P.P.P.S. I have updated the upper arms to ensure compatibility with Project Quixote, my new modular mech kit. Check it out.

https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/project-quixote-28mm-dieselpunk-modular-pre-supported-mech-kit

Best,
JBR

Demon hordes for warmaster both with and without supports using Duncan Shadow's awesome demons.

10mm demon army
See my collections for the other units; I have a unit for each of the roles in warmaster revolution and a couple of heroes. Note that this army does not inherently match one of the big four chaos gods by design, as I find them dreadfully boring.

Supports
The supports are auto generated by Prusa. The strips are densely supported, but I haven't had any failures. The worst that's happened is me breaking off an arm of one of the demons on the edges of the strip when impatiently clipping through the supports.

Why?
I just got a 3d printer and was looking to get into warmaster with some friends when I noticed that there is no ready to print demon army yet. Given my 0-level modelling skills I instead decided to use existing models to create the army; this unit is one of the outcomes of this project.

Disclaimer
To be sure: none of these models are actually mine. I am a complete hack blundering his way through blender; all I can do is resize models, fatten segments and add cylinders (you may spot some of my handiwork on other models).

Tired of seeing the enemy aircrafts hunting your troops unchallenged?? We have the solution.
Afraid of enemy long range units shooting down your BTS?? We have the solution.
Worried about that big hordes running towards you?? Yes, WE HAVE THE SOLUTION.

Here you can find 3 wonderful "solutions": anti air tank, missile launcher tank and mortar tank (note that this one is modelled after the newest version, not the classic one).

They all share the same chasis thanks to STC magic and the same turret thanks to MkHand Industries amazing work. Simply print one chasis, one turret and a pair of mirrored weapon options for the tanks you desire, or mix and match then for fun results xD.

As always, I included both supported and unsupported versions.

This is a remix with the following parts:
Track guards: https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:3647995
Skull insignia: https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:399182
Body, turret and weapons by MkHand Industries: https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/epic-scale-anti-air-artillery

UPDATE: Added a ZIP with all files in case Thingiverse does its magic again...
Apparently clicking the download all button leads to the 404 page, simply go to thing files tab and download the zip file, simple workaround for a buggy site.

UPDATE: Test printed nicely, except for the missiles that printed kind of weird, I resupported them and reuploaded the fixed files (also updated the ZIP file).

UPDATE 15/Dec/2020: The antiair cannons were too long for my like, so I added 2 more versions closer to the 40k model proportion, so now you can choose xD (also updated the ZIP file).

A radome designed to be 3D printed as terrain for 6mm tabletop gaming. These provide great scatter terrain to add detail to your military bases. It also looks great in an open field as extra cover. The top of the B version is flat and can support a unit placed on top for playability. It is 2 levels tall if you're playing a specific mecha tabletop game.

There are four files. One of each building both with and without hexes so that you can print the one that fits your playstyle. Remember to print the B version if you want the extra support pegs to support units on top for playability. I advise printing these in resin if possible because they are small enough that they don't take much resin, and the details show up smoother.

As always, tipping is appreciated at: paypal.me/rainingfire416

Notable features:
-This building goes perfectly with the other military buildings I've designed.
-Detailed design including entrance door, supported walkway, and radome design.

The model units are in mm and it is scaled such that the hexes are 33mm from flat-to-flat, which is perfect for modern hex maps using 33mm hexes. You can always resize it if your hexes are slightly smaller/larger.

Please post pictures and leave feedback if you make this yourself! I'd love to see prints and use the feedback to adjust overhangs, detail levels, etc. on this model and future ones as well.

~~~

~~~

Call it IFV, APC or just mobile cover, this little fellow helps your cannon fodder to get closer to the enemy so they can die faster. Have fun!

Included 3 chasis (standard one, standard one with rear aquila and command one) but only 1 turret.

This is a remix but, again, Thingiverse doesn´t allow me to link them properly, here are the part lists:

Chasis: By Mkhand Forgeworld
Multilaser: https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:3049352

Radar: https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:3753633

UPDATE 26/10/2020: Test printed. They print fine but I broke one of the lasguns from the array on the clean up process and ended up hating the hollowed part (a pain to clean). I will soon upload new models with tougher lasgun arrays and radar receptor, as well as more pronounced aquilas for the command body (they are barely visible).

UPDATE 28/10/2020: Added second versions for standard and command body, as promised. Also included a second version of the turret, it just has a bigger peg.
If you are upscaling the models, consider using the first ones, they are more accurate.
Test printed at 0.04 and 0.02, both went great.

A full infatry company for Epic games.

70 models, not a single repeated pose (although several are very similar xD).
It includes 6 infantry squads (1 with commissar), a company commander squad and a suppreme commander squad.
I used missile launchers instead of autocannons because I find them more dinamic for infantry on the move, I will use autocannons for the heavy weapon teams in the near future.

I have included the chitubox files in case you want to find the unsupported versions of the models.

This is a remix, but Thingiverse keeps failing to allow me link them properly, so here they are:

Infantry models: https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:3746245

Missile launcher and commissar insignia: https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:399182
Chainswords, swords and boltpistols: https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:4277183
Commissar body: I do not remember where I downloaded it from. If you are the author, please ping me to give you credit.


UPDATE 2020/10/26: Test printed. Everything went perfectly.

UPDATE 2021/01/19: Files replaced for newer versions (Comissar moved to its own thing and 1 pose repeated to replace him, sorry for that!). Ork spaceship that can be used as a Kill Kroozer or a Terror Ship in the long out-of-production game Battlefleet Gothic.

I did the following remix of the source material:
- extracted the Ork Battleship from the source
- scaled it to 100 mm length
- removed the geometry inside the model

Many of the details are obviously too tiny for most printers, so you'll probably need to do some pruning before slicing and printing it at this scale.

Note: I did not design this model. I think it was extracted from Battlefleet Gothic: Armada 2.

Updates 2020-05-15:
- I updated the title to "Ork Kroozer", as it is labeled as such in the game.
- I have fixed up the model extensively. I have removed a lot of antennae and small gubbins that wouldn't print properly at the proper scale for the board game.
- I have scaled the model down to about 7 cm, which is the same size as the original metal Kroozers.
- I have added a version with a small base attached. This is meant to be printed in one piece.
- I have added a pre-supported file of the kroozer with small base. Both the STL and Chitubox file is available.

Justification du tag SUP :

"What are you Hungry?. I just fell down a hill. I'm soaking wet. I don't have any food. I have no food on me. I have nothing on me." -Dennis Nedry

Dilophosaurus is a genus of theropod dinosaur that lived in what is now North America during the Early Jurassic, about 193 million years ago. Length was up to 23 ft long and an estimated Mass of 880 lbs.

Jurassic Park brought new recognition to the Dilophosaurus, being one of the coolest brought to life for the first film as well as my personal favorite. The Jurassic Park version shows a smaller version (could just be younger) that spit blinding venom, and had a frill that would unfurl when attacking, none of which are supported by the fossil record but did make a heck of a entertaining film so I am ok with it. This pose is meant to be reminiscent of the "fetch the stick stupid" scene in which the Dilo' looks over its shoulder at the stick. I like pose from this scene because the Dinosaur is still in its innocent puppy mode and shows off the mobility of its long neck also the frill isn't visible in that scene at all so this still fits..

You have some options to make different versions of the Dilo with the files I have provided:

 You can make a model the prints in parts that all pegs together. There is also a a high resolution fully assembled version (probably to big to properly preview with the "Thingview" sorry). It has higher quality details than most FFM printers can duplicate but if you have a resin printer or just want to play with the file to make a bigger version I feel this will be the most useful for you. I have also feature a Scaled up head it is about 1/2 the size of a real dilophosaurus or about 65%-75% the size of the Jurassic Park dilo, I printed one myself and it makes a great wall display.

As always I will promote and REWARD the first person to post a make (must enable tips on your profile for reward)

Update!: https://www.thingiverse.com/CH35C0 was the winner of this things "First Make Award" check out their page for some cool and practical designs!

Update! 2/11/19 Added a strait neck version.

His print in action! good use of meshmixer tree supports to save on cleanup.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hOrhhjOC3Zs&feature=youtu.be

If this proves popular, I will work on a version with a frill and an open mouth version. So Please post your makes, hit like, and provide feedback in the comments.

Thank you and enjoy!

Each model has been sculpted anew from the ground up, not just refined but completely reimagined, forged to embody the dark essence of excess and corruption.

Crafted exclusively for 10mm and 15mm scale, these warriors march with razor-sharp clarity: every horn, every blade, every shard of armor sculpted to strike the eye and dominate the battlefield. Their forms are designed not only for visual impact, but also for flawless, effortless printing, ensuring their terror manifests cleanly on your tabletop.

This is more than a unit—it is the culmination of years of refinement, the fifth evolution of demonic might, perfected for wargamers who demand nothing less than the extraordinary.
